  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Pricing</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki wins clearly on price. Community tutors start at around $4 per lesson, and even professional tutors rarely exceed $20 to $25 per session. This makes regular practice genuinely affordable for learners on a tight budget.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Preply starts at $10 per lesson for most tutors, with prices climbing to $50 or more for experienced, highly-rated teachers. The quality floor is higher, but so is the cost. Preply does offer subscription discounts, which can bring the effective price down if you commit to monthly lessons.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Both platforms charge per lesson with no hidden fees. Neither requires a subscription, though both incentivize regular bookings with better rates for committed learners.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Tutor Quality and Selection</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki has three categories of tutors: community tutors, professional tutors, and language exchange partners. Community tutors are typically fluent speakers without formal teaching qualifications. Professional tutors have verified credentials like TEFL or teaching degrees. Language exchange partners are learners themselves who want to trade languages.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Preply only lists professional tutors, which means every teacher on the platform has been vetted for qualifications. This reduces variability in quality. Preply also has a stronger selection of native English speakers from the US, UK, Canada, and Australia.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">For sheer variety, iTalki wins. For guarantee of professional credentials and native-speaker access, Preply has the edge.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Learning Experience</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki gives you freedom. You pick your tutor, agree on what to study, and work at your own pace. This model works well for conversational practice and learners who know what they want to focus on. The quality of each lesson depends heavily on the tutor you choose.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Preply provides more structure. New learners can take a placement test that places them at the right level. Tutors follow standardized lesson plans aligned to CEFR levels. This makes Preply feel more like a traditional language school and less like hiring a freelance tutor.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">If you want flexibility and personal control over your lessons, iTalki is the better fit. If you prefer a guided path with clear learning objectives, Preply is worth the higher price.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Platform Features</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Both platforms offer built-in video calling, mobile apps, and scheduling tools. The core experience is similar on both.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">iTalki has an optional community feature where learners can join group classes and language exchange sessions for free. This adds extra value outside of paid 1-on-1 lessons.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Preply includes a skill assessment tool and lesson resources that tutors can share with students. The platform also has a dedicated business English course, which iTalki does not offer as formally.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Pros and Cons</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">iTalki Pros</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-4">
    <li>Lower prices, starting at $4 per lesson</li>
    <li>More tutor variety and flexibility</li>
    <li>Language exchange partners available for free</li>
    <li>Larger selection of tutors from non-traditional markets</li>
    <li>No pressure to commit to one tutor</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">iTalki Cons</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-6">
    <li>Quality varies more between tutors</li>
    <li>Community tutors lack formal qualifications</li>
    <li>Less structured curriculum</li>
    <li>Fewer native English speaker options compared to Preply</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Preply Pros</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-4">
    <li>All tutors are professionally vetted</li>
    <li>Strong native English speaker selection</li>
    <li>Structured curriculum with CEFR alignment</li>
    <li>Dedicated business English course</li>
    <li>Better refund and cancellation policies</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Preply Cons</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-600 mb-8">
    <li>Higher starting price ($10 per lesson)</li>
    <li>Less tutor variety</li>
    <li>Feels less personal than iTalki</li>
    <li>No free community features or language exchange</li>
    <li>Can feel more like a school than a marketplace</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Which Should You Choose?</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Choose iTalki if:</strong> You are on a budget and want affordable access to regular practice. You prefer flexibility over structure and enjoy building relationships with individual tutors. You are comfortable vetting tutors yourself by reading reviews and trying trial lessons.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed"><strong>Choose Preply if:</strong> You want guaranteed professional credentials from every tutor. You prefer a structured learning path with clear goals. You are willing to pay more for consistency and quality assurance. You specifically want native English speakers from the US, UK, Canada, or Australia.</p>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Both platforms are legitimate and well-established. The right choice depends on your budget, learning style, and goals. Many learners start with iTalki for affordable practice and move to Preply when they are ready to invest more in structured progress.</p>
